Read in and compile dendro files

load(file = "../../data/GrowthMortality/live_pipo_rwl.Rdata")
rwlp <- rwl_live_pipo
load(file = "../../data/GrowthMortality/live_abco_rwl.Rdata")
rwla <- rwl_live_abco

Plot data before detrending

Gather/restructure

PIPO

rwlp2 <- rwlp %>% 
  mutate(year = row.names(rwlp))
rwlp2 <- gather(rwlp2, key = "tree", value = "growth", 1:ncol(rwlp)) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(growth))
head(rwlp2)
##   year tree    growth
## 1 2012 106B 0.4433333
## 2 2013 106B 0.3500000
## 3 2014 106B 0.3966667
## 4 2015 106B 0.4033333
## 5 2016 106B 0.2866667
## 6 2013 107B 0.3533333
rwlp3 <- rwlp2 %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  mutate(means = mean(na.omit(growth))) %>% 
  mutate(n = n()) %>% 
  ungroup()
rwlp3_summary <- rwlp3 %>% 
  group_by(tree) %>% 
  summarize(n = n()) %>% 
  arrange(desc(n))
rwlp3_summary

Plot by # of rings in the series

PIPO

Pines with 8 years:

ggplot(rwlp3 %>% filter(tree %in%  rwlp3_summary$tree[1:6])) + 
  stat_smooth(aes(x = year, y = growth, group = tree, col = tree), method = "lm", fill = "white",se = F)+
  geom_line(aes(x = year, y = growth, group = tree, col = tree), size = 1, linetype = "dashed")

2 pos, 4 neg

Pines with 7 years:

ggplot(rwlp3 %>% filter(tree %in%  unlist(rwlp3_summary[rwlp3_summary$n == 7,"tree"]))) + 
  stat_smooth(aes(x = year, y = growth, group = tree, col = tree), method = "lm", fill = "white",se = F)+
  geom_line(aes(x = year, y = growth, group = tree, col = tree), size = 1, linetype = "dashed")

5 pos, 3 neg

Pines with 6 years:

ggplot(rwlp3 %>% filter(tree %in%  unlist(rwlp3_summary[rwlp3_summary$n == 6,"tree"]))) + 
  stat_smooth(aes(x = year, y = growth, group = tree, col = tree), method = "lm", fill = "white",se = F)+
  geom_line(aes(x = year, y = growth, group = tree, col = tree), size = 1, linetype = "dashed")

5 pos, 8 neg, 2 zero

Of the pines with 6, 7, or 8 rings, 12 have positive slopes, 15 have negative slopes, and 2 have slopes very near zero. In other words, nearly half have positive or zero slopes, so applying a negative exponential curve doesnt make much sense. Im going to apply a horizontal line curve instead.

  geom_line(aes(x = year, y = growth, group = tree, col = tree), size = 1, linetype = "dashed")

5 pos, 3 neg

Of the firs with 8-13 rings, 13 have positive slopes and 11 have negative slopes. In other words, over half have positive slopes, so applying a negative exponential curve doesnt make much sense. Im going to apply a horizontal line curve instead.

Plot detrended seedlings

Reshape detrended means with error bars

PIPO

dfp <- as.data.frame(t(rwlp_dt))
dfp$tree <- row.names(dfp)
dfp <- gather(dfp, key = "Year", value = "growth_detrended", c(1:13))
dfp <- dfp %>% 
  filter(!is.na(growth_detrended))

Take out trees with very few rings

Find tallies of lengths of each trees series
dfp %>% 
  group_by(tree) %>% 
  summarize(n_rings = n()) %>% 
  group_by(n_rings) %>% 
  summarize(n_n = n()) %>% 
  arrange(n_rings)

Plot

PIPO

Calculate standard errors

dfpstd <- dfp %>% 
  group_by(Year) %>% 
  mutate(mean_gr_year = mean(growth_detrended)) %>% 
  mutate(n_year = n()) %>% 
  mutate(stderror = sd(growth_detrended)/sqrt(n_year)) %>% 
  mutate(min = mean_gr_year-2*stderror) %>% 
  mutate(max = mean_gr_year+2*stderror)
dfpstd

Plot

ggplot(dfpstd) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = as.numeric(Year), y = mean_gr_year), col = "red")+
  geom_line(aes(x = as.numeric(Year), y = mean_gr_year), col = "red")+
  geom_errorbar(aes(x = as.numeric(Year),ymin = min, ymax = max), width = .2, col = "gray")+
  geom_line(aes(x = as.numeric(Year), y = min), col = "gray")+
  geom_line(aes(x = as.numeric(Year), y = max), col = "gray")+
  ggtitle("PIPO standardized means +/- 2 SE")

ABCO

Calculate standard errors

dfastd <- dfa %>% 
  group_by(Year) %>% 
  mutate(mean_gr_year = mean(growth_detrended)) %>% 
  mutate(n_year = n()) %>% 
  mutate(stderror = sd(growth_detrended)/sqrt(n_year)) %>% 
  mutate(min = mean_gr_year-2*stderror) %>% 
  mutate(max = mean_gr_year+2*stderror)
